node.text:
When two towers fell, we rose as one and vowed to never forget the loved ones who did not come home.
 
The @911memorial is doing tremendous work to ensure a new generation will learn the lessons of 9/11.
 
Join us in commemorating the 20th anniversary on Saturday 9/11/21 by taking a picture of the sky — no matter the weather or where you are — and sharing it with #NeverForget911.  Neverforget.org

The @911memorial & Museum Visionary Network is ensuring the next generation never forgets the lives lost, the sacrifices made, and the ongoing consequences of that day. 

It’s an important mission—one I am glad to support. If you're between the ages of 21 and 45 and want to deepen your connection to the 9/11 Memorial & Museum and ensure that future generations remember 9/11 and its aftermath, join the Visionary Network at the link in bio.

In response to the greatest challenge to public education in generations, the Biden administration needs to get kids back in the classroom without delay—and push states to run universal summer school.

For our kids, and our future, there is nothing more important. Read why at my link in bio.

node.title: Pandemic Recovery Should Include Summer School

node.text:
After 9/11, people were wondering if the city's best days were beyond it. Now, those doubts have returned. 

It's possible to bring the city back faster and stronger than anyone expected - and now, I believe @EricAdamsforNYC has what it takes to do it again. 

He has the courage to stand up and take on tough issues and special interests. 

He's pragmatic - so he'll focus on solutions, not ideology. 

And he's a big believer in using data to inform decision-making. 

I couldn't be more optimistic about the city's future - and it will take all of us pulling together. Eric Adams has my full support - and I hope he'll have yours, too.

Christo and Jeanne-Claude were a visionary artistic team who had a special ability to transform a space and make it new, while also bringing people together. I'm looking forward to visiting their last project, "L'Arc de Triomphe, Wrapped" in Paris. 

When I was mayor, I had the honor of working with @christojeanneclaude when they installed "The Gates," which helped New Yorkers and millions of visitors experience Central Park in a different way at a time when our city was still recovering from the 9/11 attacks.
 
Now, it’s fitting that they will once again provide a source of inspiration during a difficult time. It's exciting that Parisians and visitors will be able to experience this event in person — and everyone around the world will be able to join in as well, by downloading the free Bloomberg Connects app. 

🎥: Courtesy Centre des monuments nationaux 
📷: Wolfgang Volz

node.text: It’s hard to believe 20 years have passed since 9/11. Today we honor all the lives we lost – and the countless acts of valor, kindness, and heroism that inspired the world. node.text:
September 11, 2001 was primary day in New York City’s mayoral election. The sky was bright blue. The weather was picture perfect. I voted and went to campaign headquarters. That’s where we first saw the news that a plane had hit the World Trade Center. 
 
The days that followed were dark. And they stretched into weeks and months. But as we grieved, we also found inspiration in the stories of heroism and the spirit of unity that lifted us up. 
 
Seven weeks after the attacks, I was elected mayor. And it was the honor of my life to be given the chance to help lead our city back from the brink. 
 
The @911Memorial and Museum serve as vital links to our past, and to our future, too. 
 
And today, as our nation and the whole world battles another crisis, we must remember how we – people from every country, every background, and every faith – joined together as one: to heal, to recover, and to rebuild, in ways that made us stronger than ever. 

Join @911memorial in commemorating the 20th anniversary today by taking a picture of the sky and sharing it with #NeverForget911. Neverforget.org
